Description.val:
Jet Assisted Take Offs (JATOs) are solid propellant rocket motors used to launch BQM-74 target drones in support of Combat System Ship Qualification Trials (CSSQT) for Navy surface ships and other fleet events.

[P40A / OTHER COSTS]: Other Cost includes Production Engineering Support (PES), Integrated Logistics Support (ILS), Reliability Life (i.e. Safety and Product Improvement Program (PIP), Quality Assurance and Acceptance Testing.

Justification.val:
FY15 Congressional Reduction of $2.76M due to Program Delay arising from a MK117 Jet Assisted Take-Off (JATO) motor production stoppage in 2012 when the rocket motor propellant grain failed qualification testing.  A recently completed Engineering Investigation (EI) supports production re-start in FY15.

The FY16 baseline funding is required for MK117 procurement to enable continued BQM-74 target operations through FY20. Without FY16 baseline funding, JATO production deliveries will be unable to match anticipated expenditures, limiting the capability of the Navy surface fleet to conduct pre-deployment training.  Although the MK117 Mod 0 is the only JATO currently being procured, they have been out of production since 2012 when the rocket motor propellant grain failed qualification testing. A recently completed Engineering Investigation (EI) supports production re-start in FY15 and NSWC Indian Head production capacity supports deliveries of all remaining MK117 JATOs procured with funding from FY10 through FY14.  The deliveries of these units procured with prior year funds, will commence in FY16 with completion in FY17.

FiscalYear.@footnote: Due to PDOCs limitations, only 24 months can be shown in the delivery schedule. In August 2012, 308 units were delivered; these deliveries are recorded in August 2016. The remaining 202 units will be delivered upon receipt of propellant and at completion of First Article Testing starting in September 2016. Deliveries will complete in October 2015.

Nominal manufacturing lead-time is 18 months, but FY10 - FY14 production units are on hold due to propellant grain manufacturing issues. Recently completed Engineering Investigation (EI) supports production re-start in FY15.  NSWC production capacity supports delivery of FY10-FY14 units starting in FY16, with completion in FY17.
